{
  "texts": [
    "We subsequently used the fact-checking tweets and their REFERENCED_TWEETS field (see [81]) to retrieve the parent tweets, i.e., the fact-checked tweets.",
    "In accordance with Vosoughi et al., we excluded parent tweets that (i) were not in English or (ii) themselves contained a link to a fact-checking page.",
    "We slightly diverged from Vosoughi et al. 's approach by also taking into account tweets that are not first level, i.e., we also considered replies to replies.",
    "This allowed us to capture more data, aiming to increase the accuracy of the ACR method.",
    "Analyses were stopped whenever the number of fact-checked tweets fell below n = 30."
  ]
}